	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've read a number of post here talking about how the main job of a warrior is to take damage and the amount of damage you do is not all that important.&nbsp;&nbsp;Now granted at lvl 30 I can't talk about what happens in high lvl groups...but I do have a few coments or questons<br>If the monk, rogue, or wiz, is doing a lot more damage over time to the mob than the warrior wouldn't the mob be beating on them  instead of the war?  Yes warriors can taunt, but taunting will not keep a mob on you when you are bing out damaged by another player.  <br>So if you are being out damaged by monks and rogues how do you take the beating?<br>What percent of the time is there a rogue in your pick up groups?  What percent ofthe time is there a monk in your pickup groups?  <br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
