	   <tr><td colspan=2>EASILY.&nbsp;&nbsp;The warrior taunt is VERY potent.  first off Rogues have EVADE. it lets the mob who is aggro on them drop down the aggro list and the mob will face another opponent.  While wizards do massive damage they will usually wait till the warrior does a decent amount of damage so that the mob will not attack the wizard.  beleive me when a wizard decides to nuke of the bat he will end up being a stiff.  Here's a good example and im not kidding. right now I have about 1233 attack with a decent group and I am level 57..  Theres a 58 ranger with his FA and a 56 Pally with his FA with a 60 rogue with Fa backing us up.  In almost everyfight I was the only one to take omre then a quarter of a bubble of damage. This is becuase of the rogue evade and rangers have a spell called JOLT which makes the mob attack the next target as oppose to them.   <br><br>AS far as dueling goes yes melee classes get the shaft.  BUT if you are IN A DUNGEON without alot of moveability you can actually kick some caster ass!  The best thing to do is to build up on your MR gear like MIth arms and leggins and you'll be able to take down wizards and chanters with ease.. even druids since they can't use half of their spells and sows and things like that won't work.  It's tricky but you can do it.  At level 55 warriors get stun kick.. Stun a wizard watch him spin then unload on him with low delay weapons.  Many of the casters have high spells which can kill you quickly but they also take a long time to cast so make sure that you keep dogging them to death.  As far as dueling paladins it's not smart since they can easily lay on hand or they may have the damn stun bracer.  <br><br><br>Oh and for those of you who complain that casters are so powerful just wait til you get high level.  Whenever there is a big train or a caster messes up and ends up getting aggro he is DEAD.  There is no time to do a heal when a caster gets attacked by three or four mobs who quad for 150.  Also do a poll find out how many days played a caster has compared to the days you have played and chances are you have played ALOT less.  I could never play a caster... they just die to damn easily.  I am a fighter.. I like to be in the center of battle and not sit down and med all the time.   LONG LIVE THE WARRIOR CLASS and MELEE CLASSES BAHAHHAH<br>     -JG<br>  Japakazol Garassjulioson<br>  57 Halfling warrior<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
